{"key":"post-7575625","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7575625</id>\n<content>FGL&lt;br /&gt;Hot MEA with Gentmycin sulphate as antibiotic is what I use.  Normally, I let the agar cool until I can hold the bottle to pour without any heat protection for my hands. If I'm trying to pour over bacterial contamination, I'll pour it a bit hotter.  The idea is to knock the bacteria back with heat, but the stronger mushroom mycelium will survive the hot agar to grow up through to the top.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7575648</next>\n<prev>7575610</prev>\n<first>5702019</first>\n<last>7575652</last>\n<when>1193751161</when>\n<utime>10/30/07 04:32 PM</utime>\n</post>"}